{"key":"processedPost-10330479","value":{"id":10330479,"first":10328498,"last":14408003,"when":1242196646,"utime":"05/13/09 09:37 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />how would taping up holes LOWER humidity?</blockquote><br />Assuming you put 1/4\" holes every 2\" around all six sides per the tek, it will work as advertised.&nbsp; Just so I don't have to type it again, here's the <a href=\"/forums/showflat.php/Number/6880451#6880451\" class=\"pp\" target=\"_blank\">engineering behind the terrarium</a>.&nbsp; Remember, air enters from the bottom and rises to the air space above.&nbsp; As it travels through the perlite, it absorbs moisture.<br />Don't forget, fresh air exchange is the number 1 pinning trigger.&nbsp; Don't get hung up on humidity.&nbsp; If necessary mist, but keep the holes open. Also know that the humidity right at the surface of the perlite where the cakes sit will be higher than farther above.&nbsp; None of my shotgun terrariums has fallen below 90% humidity with the lids completely removed.","title":"Re: Trouble with humidity"}}